This uses a known workaround/hack to convert a sheet metal body
to a normal solid body. See BRepBody.isSheetMetal. The approach
is to use a boundary fill on the sheet metal bodies, you can do
this from the UI but then you must visually check all of the
check boxes on the objects in the design, which is difficult
and error prone for large amounts of cells. This just does
the operations and selects all cells, creating all solids.
